Shells a deployment-configured LLM adapter command and mediates the JSON request/response contract: `{"system": <prompt>, "user": <dynamic input>, "model": <model name>}` in via stdin, completion text out via stdout. The agent never executes inline—all LLM calls go through this boundary.

`Agent` is a trait; `SubprocessAgent` is the production impl. The command itself comes from `CTX_AGENT_CMD` (env var first, then `.env` fallback), never hardcoded. An `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` found in `.env` is injected into the child's environment only—never into this process—so secrets stay out of the shell. The `.env` parser strips comments, blanks, and optional quotes (`KEY="value"` or `KEY='value'`), and ignores unknown keys.

`SubprocessAgent::complete(system, user, model)` spawns `sh -c <command>`, sends JSON-serialized `Payload` to its stdin, collects stdout, validates non-empty and exit code 0, then sleeps 1 second (`MIN_REQUEST_SPACING`) before returning. Empty output or nonzero exit becomes `SummError::Agent`. Stderr is captured for error messages but not returned on success. The request/response is not factored—it's one synchronous I/O transaction to keep the contract atomic.